physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Right leg paresthesias, inguinal swelling, extreme fatigue.
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: CD4 count increased to 174 cells/mm3 and viral load fell to 4,150 copies/mL within 4 weeks of therapy initiation.
Absolute eosinophilia persisted; repeat lymph node biopsy revealed Wuchereria bancrofti.
